<div id="main-article" class="article-content retro-folders">
<p>


</p><div class="quoteright" style="width:226px;"><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Webcomic/WhatBirdsKnow" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Webcomic/WhatBirdsKnow"><div class="lazy_load_img_box" style="padding-top:124.78%"><img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/images/wbk1_5573.png" class="embeddedimage" border="0" alt="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/images/wbk1_5573.png" width="226" height="282"></div></a></div>
<p></p><div class="indent"><em>"Sexy women would 'happen' to be topless in the 1970s movies for no better reason than that everyone agreed, including themselves, that their breasts were a genuine pleasure to regard &mdash; the most beautiful naturally occurring shapes in nature, I believe. Now we see breasts only in serious films, for expressing reasons. There's been such a comeback for the strategically positioned bed sheet, you'd think we were back in the 1950s."</em>
<div class="indent">&mdash; <strong><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/RogerEbert" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/RogerEbert">Roger Ebert</a></strong>, <a class="urllink" href="http://rogerebert.suntimes.com/apps/pbcs.dll/article?AID=/20091014/REVIEWS/910149998">reviewing<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/BlackDynamite" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/BlackDynamite">Black Dynamite</a></em>
</div></div><div class="proper-ad-unit mobile-ad square_ad"><h6 class="ad-caption">Advertisement:</h6><div id="proper-ad-tvtropes_mobile_ad_1"><script>propertag.cmd.push(function() { proper_display('tvtropes_mobile_ad_1'); })</script></div></div><p>A character who is nude in bed uses the bedsheet to cover their private parts. They may be in the morning after a night of passion, or have been <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UndressingTheUnconscious" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UndressingTheUnconscious">undressed and left resting in bed</a> or even simply be <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SleepsInTheNude" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SleepsInTheNude">sleeping in the buff</a>. The nude character might get out of bed and drag along the sheet pulled from the bed to avoid exposing nudity to a sexual partner (or even an empty room) and, coincidentally, to the viewer. They may even wrap the sheet in such a way as to make a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ImprovisedClothes" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ImprovisedClothes">makeshift dress</a>, instead of putting on some clothes or a robe. A character that has found themselves without clothes for any reason may also make use (or be given) some kind of bedsheet, blanket or cloth for them to covers themselves with.
</p><p>Another frequent variation is during sex scenes when a sheet is used to strategically cover the couple's nudity or any explicit sexual act <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CoitusEnsues" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CoitusEnsues">while they're making love</a>. In post-sex scenes, couples will often have the bedsheet draped over their bodies, with the sheet usually falling low to the man's waist (exposing his <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShirtlessScene" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShirtlessScene">bare chest</a>) but having the woman's bust covered up. Apparently, L-shaped blankets, also known as the <em>His 'n' Hers Bedsheet</em>, are a fad in fictionland. There's also a unisex bed sheet that also falls to the woman's waist that can either: have her laying on her stomach so as to only expose her <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ToplessnessFromTheBack" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ToplessnessFromTheBack">Toplessness from the Back</a>, have her still wearing a bra or simply leaving her breasts uncovered. The latter was very popular during <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheSeventies" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheSeventies">The '70s</a> and early <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheEighties" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheEighties">Eighties</a>. Even media that freely show topless nudity, will frequently have sex scenes that feature sheets tightly wrapped around the waists of the two actors simulating coitus.
</p><div class="proper-ad-unit mobile-ad square_ad"><h6 class="ad-caption">Advertisement:</h6><div id="proper-ad-tvtropes_mobile_ad_2"><script>propertag.cmd.push(function() { proper_display('tvtropes_mobile_ad_2'); })</script></div></div><p>Media that feature corpses for autopsies or surgeries (such as <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PoliceProcedural" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PoliceProcedural">Police Procedural</a> and <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MedicalDrama" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MedicalDrama">Medical Dramas</a>) also frequently have bedsheets draped over them to preserve their modesty or cover wounds. Sometimes the sheets will <em>only</em> cover the nudity while the gore of the body's wounds may still be in full display.
</p><p>Done well, audiences won't even really notice. It's not unusual for people to have a sense of modesty, even when alone or with a lover. Or they may simply be cold. However, done poorly it can be incredibly jarring and break viewers' suspension of disbelief.
</p><p>While this is a censorship trope, it is also a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Fanservice" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Fanservice">Fanservice</a> one, as the idea of a character <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheissTitillationTheory" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheissTitillationTheory">wearing solely a bedsheet is titillating in and of itself.</a> To the point <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FanserviceModel" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FanserviceModel">Fanservice Models</a> posing wearing only a bedsheet became a somewhat common modeling "<a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FanserviceCostumes" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FanserviceCostumes">attire</a>" that features in many magazines and promotional material. A character who is <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheTease" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheTease">The Tease</a> may even invoke this <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/InUniverse" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/InUniverse">In-Universe</a>, as wearing only a sheet is a popular way to show your potential sexual partner one is <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ReadyForLovemaking" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ReadyForLovemaking">Ready for Lovemaking</a>. A character dressed in only a sheet is also a common way to make someone look <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SexDressed" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SexDressed">Sex Dressed</a>.
</p><div class="proper-ad-unit mobile-ad square_ad"><h6 class="ad-caption">Advertisement:</h6><div id="proper-ad-tvtropes_mobile_ad_3"><script>propertag.cmd.push(function() { proper_display('tvtropes_mobile_ad_3'); })</script></div></div><p>See <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RightThroughHisPants" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RightThroughHisPants">Right Through His Pants</a> for when characters are wearing pants or underwear in situations where you would expect them to be nude. See <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BankruptcyBarrel" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BankruptcyBarrel">Bankruptcy Barrel</a>, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HandOrObjectUnderwear" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HandOrObjectUnderwear">Hand-or-Object Underwear</a>, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ModestyTowel" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ModestyTowel">Modesty Towel</a> and <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ModestyRags" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ModestyRags">Modesty Rags</a> for other objects that can be used to preserve one's modesty. Compare <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SceneryCensor" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SceneryCensor">Scenery Censor</a>, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShouldersUpNudity" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShouldersUpNudity">Shoulders-Up Nudity</a> or <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ToplessnessFromTheBack" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ToplessnessFromTheBack">Toplessness from the Back</a> for other ways of showing nudity without showing <em>nudity</em>.
</p><p></p><hr><p></p><h2>Examples</h2>
<p></p><div class="folderlabel" onclick="toggleAllFolders();">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;open/close all folders&nbsp; </div>
<p></p><div class="folderlabel" onclick="togglefolder('folder0');">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Advertising&nbsp;</div><div id="folder0" class="folder" isfolder="true" style="display:block;">
<p></p><ul><li> A 2011 <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/UsefulNotes/SuperBowl" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/UsefulNotes/SuperBowl">Super Bowl</a> <a class="urllink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Tap4J9nT96U">ad<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a> for the mattress company "Sealy" feature many couples <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PostCoitalCollapse" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PostCoitalCollapse">collapsing into bed after sex</a>, each with their own Modesty Bedsheet wrapped around them.
</li></ul><p></p></div>
<p></p><div class="folderlabel" onclick="togglefolder('folder1');">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Anime &amp; Manga&nbsp;</div><div id="folder1" class="folder" isfolder="true" style="display:block;">
<p></p><ul><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/ZeroZeroNineOne" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/ZeroZeroNineOne">009-1</a></em>: Mylene Hoffman/Agent 009-1 is shown using Modesty Bedsheets (combined with <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ToplessnessFromTheBack" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ToplessnessFromTheBack">Toplessness from the Back</a>) on several occasions. In fact, she was wearing nothing but a bedsheet in <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NakedOnArrival" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NakedOnArrival">her very first appearance in the very first episode</a>. They usually end up <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ClothingDamage" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ClothingDamage">being torn to shreds</a> due to her <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TorpedoTits" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TorpedoTits">Torpedo Tits</a>.
</li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/Berserk" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/Berserk">Berserk</a></em>:
<ul><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SubvertedTrope" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SubvertedTrope">Subverted</a>. The anime version briefly used a cape during <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> Guts and Casca's love scene</span>. But a few seconds later...
</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ZigZagged" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ZigZagged">Zig-Zagged</a> when Griffith and Charlotte sleep together, we get various explicit shots of the act, but the scene ends with a tame shot of Charlotte sleeping with the sheet covering her nudity, albeit with <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ToplessnessFromTheBack" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ToplessnessFromTheBack">Toplessness from the Back</a>.
</li></ul></li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/BloodPlus" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/BloodPlus">Blood+</a></em>: When an unconscious Saya is rescued by Solomon, he takes her to his apartment and <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UndressingTheUnconscious" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UndressingTheUnconscious">undresses her to treat her wounds</a>. She wakes up naked under some bedsheets, which she wraps around herself before walking around the place searching for her clothes. He soon shows up and offers her a fancy <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PimpedOutDress" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PimpedOutDress">Pimped-Out Dress</a> which she <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HatesWearingDresses" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HatesWearingDresses">dislikes only slightly less</a> than just the bedsheet.
</li><li> All versions of <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/BubblegumCrisis" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/BubblegumCrisis">Bubblegum Crisis</a></em> show Sylia Stingray <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SleepsInTheNude" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SleepsInTheNude">Sleeps in the Nude</a> but covered with a modesty sheet. The original version is more blatant showing <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShesGotLegs" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShesGotLegs">her bare legs</a> and shoulders despite the bedsheet, whereas the remake only opts for <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShouldersUpNudity" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShouldersUpNudity">Shoulders-Up Nudity</a>.
</li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/CodeGeass" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/CodeGeass">Code Geass</a></em>: When Villetta first wakes up after being shot and losing her memory, she finds herself naked <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WakingUpElsewhere" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WakingUpElsewhere">in Ohgi's bed</a>, since he <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UndressingTheUnconscious" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UndressingTheUnconscious">took off her clothes to patch up her wounds</a>. The bedsheet slide down when she sits up, and when she notices it, she has a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NakedFreakOut" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NakedFreakOut">Naked Freak-Out</a> and picks the sheet back up to cover herself.
</li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/DancougarNova" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/DancougarNova">Dancougar Nova</a></em>: Aoi is shown to sleep in "<a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SleepsInTheNude" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SleepsInTheNude">her original</a>" in episode 2 when she wakes up in a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CatapultNightmare" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CatapultNightmare">Catapult Nightmare</a>, with a Modesty Bedsheet covering all important bits. Riruri calls in her <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/VideoPhone" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/VideoPhone">Video Phone</a> moments later, and Aoi wraps herself up in the sheets and walks around her house like that while conversing with Riruri.
</li><li> Used by Kiyomi Takada in <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/DeathNote" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/DeathNote">Death Note</a></em>. <span class="spoiler" title="you can set spoilers visible by default on your profile"> After Mello kidnaps and strips her, but she still manages to kill him since <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/VictoriasSecretCompartment" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/VictoriasSecretCompartment">she hid a piece of the Death Note in her bra</a>, she wraps herself in a bedsheet and tries to contact Light... <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/YouHaveOutlivedYourUsefulness" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/YouHaveOutlivedYourUsefulness">who makes her burn herself to death</a>.</span>
</li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/DragonautTheResonance" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/DragonautTheResonance">Dragonaut: The Resonance</a></em>: In the second episode, Jin is knocked unconscious by Sieglinde's <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BattleButler" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BattleButler">Battle Butler</a> and <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WakingUpElsewhere" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WakingUpElsewhere">wakes up in a bed in bunker room</a> with <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UndressingTheUnconscious" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UndressingTheUnconscious">all of his clothes gone</a> save for a bedsheet. He wraps the bedsheet around his waist and starts looking around, until Sieglinde enters the room and startles him, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WardrobeMalfunction" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WardrobeMalfunction">causing his sheet to slip down the floor</a> and giving her a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NakedFirstImpression" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NakedFirstImpression">Naked First Impression</a>. She promptly nicknames him "<a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TeenyWeenie" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TeenyWeenie">Little man</a>".
</li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/FairyTail" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/FairyTail">Fairy Tail</a></em>
<ul><li> Lucy ends up having to cover herself this way after having to do some <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IntimateHealing" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IntimateHealing">Intimate Healing</a> on Natsu while he's in a coma.
</li><li> During the "<a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Recap/FairyTailTartarosArc" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Recap/FairyTailTartarosArc">Tartaros Arc</a>", Ky&ocirc;ka says she's going to "<a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SexForServices" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SexForServices">take care</a>" of Seilah for a job well done. The next time we see Seilah, she's in bed wearing nothing but a sated smile while under a bedsheet
</li></ul></li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VisualNovel/FateStayNight" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VisualNovel/FateStayNight">Fate/stay night</a></em>
<ul><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/FateGrandOrder" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/FateGrandOrder">Fate/Grand Order</a></em>: The anime opening of <em>Cosmos in the Lostbelt</em> shows Mash Kyrielight <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SleepsInTheNude" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SleepsInTheNude">sleeping naked in her bed</a> with a bedsheet preserving her modesty. Ironically she doesn't purposely keep the bedsheet covering herself with her hands when she sits, but the sheet is unintentionally brought up as an effect of her <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GagBoobs" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GagBoobs">breasts being large enough that the blanket gets caught on them</a> as she rises, without her having to even do anything to keep it there.
</li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/FateKaleidLinerPrismaIllya" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/FateKaleidLinerPrismaIllya">Fate/kaleid liner PRISMA&#9734;ILLYA</a></em>: In one of the specials, Erika goes to Angelica's room at night to talk to her and finds her <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SleepsInTheNude" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SleepsInTheNude">sleeping in the buff</a> under the bedsheets. But Angelica averts the "drag the sheet with her" part of the trope, having <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShamelessFanserviceGirl" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShamelessFanserviceGirl">no qualms about getting up and standing in her full, glory to talk to Erika</a>, with her nudity being instead concealed via <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LensFlareCensor" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LensFlareCensor">Lens Flare Censor</a>.
</li></ul></li><li> In episode 6 of the <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/FlameOfRecca" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/FlameOfRecca">Flame of Recca</a></em> anime, Yanagi <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WakingUpElsewhere" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WakingUpElsewhere">wakes up to find herself in a huge bedroom</a> after being kidnapped by Kurei's men. She's also <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UndressingTheUnconscious" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UndressingTheUnconscious">had all of her clothes removed while she was unconscious</a> and is naked save for a bedsheet, which she wraps herself around in while walking around the room until <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/StealthHiBye" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/StealthHiBye">Koganei suddenly appears behind her</a> with clothes neatly folded for her.
</li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/FruitsBasket" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/FruitsBasket">Fruits Basket</a></em>: When the Horse Rin turns back into her human form, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShapeshiftingExcludesClothing" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShapeshiftingExcludesClothing">she has no clothes on</a> so Tohru gives Rin a bedsheet to cover her nude body.
</li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/FullmetalAlchemist" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/FullmetalAlchemist">Fullmetal Alchemist</a></em>: <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SubvertedTrope" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SubvertedTrope">Subverted</a>, Hawkeye is under a sheet in bed making strangely sexual giggling noises but it turns out she's getting her feet licked by her dog Black Hayate and is alone and fully dressed.
</li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/LightNovel/GoblinSlayer" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/LightNovel/GoblinSlayer">Goblin Slayer</a></em>: After suffering gruesome injuries that left Goblin Slayer <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AlmostDeadGuy" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AlmostDeadGuy">at death's door</a>, he was healed with Resurrection, a miracle that <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IntimateHealing" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/IntimateHealing">requires the target to sleep naked in the same bed with a Maiden</a> and the bedsheets keep him, the Priestess and the Sword Maiden covered during the ritual.
</li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/HighschoolOfTheDead" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/HighschoolOfTheDead">Highschool of the Dead</a></em>: After Rei injures her back, she spends an entire episode stuck in bed clad in Modesty Bedsheet due to getting massage therapy. It deeply embarrasses her when the entire group decides to hold a reunion in the room when she's stuck there half-naked.
