<p></p><ul><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PlayedWith" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PlayedWith">Played With</a> in the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WerewolfWorks" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WerewolfWorks">YA werewolf series</a> by Steve Feasey, alternately titled <em><a class="createlink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/Changeling" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/Changeling">Changeling</a></em> or <em><a class="createlink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/Wereling" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/Wereling">Wereling</a>.</em> The first book begins with Trey, who lives in a group home, waking up to find his bedroom trashed <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AlternateIdentityAmnesia" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AlternateIdentityAmnesia">for some reason</a>. He gets into a fight with a bullying caregiver about it and only belatedly remembers <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShapeshiftingExcludesClothing" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShapeshiftingExcludesClothing">that he's naked</a>. He quickly <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HandOrObjectUnderwear" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HandOrObjectUnderwear">covers himself with a quilt</a> and pulls his shorts on under it.
