<p></p><div class="folderlabel" onclick="togglefolder('folder15');">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Web Original&nbsp;</div><div id="folder15" class="folder" isfolder="true" style="display:block;">
<p></p><ul><li> The tradition mocked in <a class="urllink" href="http://johnsu.deviantart.com/art/Aerie-Kyoudai-32530139">this<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Website/DeviantArt" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Website/DeviantArt">Deviation</a>.
</li><li> The L-shaped sheet is skewered in <a class="urllink" href="http://www.cracked.com/blog/4-products-that-only-exist-in-movies">this<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Website/Cracked" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Website/Cracked">Cracked</a></em> article, <a class="urllink" href="http://www.collegehumor.com/article/6943815/6-super-hot-sex-moves-from-pg-13-movies">this<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Website/CollegeHumor" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Website/CollegeHumor">CollegeHumor</a></em> article, and <a class="urllink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1pMvzYZx2h0">this Cracked video<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a>. The <em>Cracked</em> video also skewers over clich&eacute;s like the <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GilliganCut" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/GilliganCut">Gilligan Cut</a>, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AdBreakDoubleTake" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AdBreakDoubleTake">sitcoms returning from commercial breaks with the last line of dialogue that was said beforehand</a>, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MrExposition" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MrExposition">forced exposition</a>, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CoincidentalBroadcast" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CoincidentalBroadcast">TV broadcasts coming on that conveniently have information for the character</a>, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WakeUpMakeUp" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/WakeUpMakeUp">Wake Up Make Up</a>, and more:
<div class="indent"><em>"You're in bed with an amazing woman with whom you've just had tremendous, beautiful-people-sex. All is going well until you realize that, post-coitus, you'll still have to share a bed in your combined nudity. It's too warm to go completely under the covers, but that doesn't mean you should have to stare at her disgusting, perfectly sculpted breasts while you're trying to sleep, right? His n' Hers has the answer."</em>
</div></li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WebAnimation/DeadFantasy" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WebAnimation/DeadFantasy">Dead Fantasy</a></em>: In a preview for the canceled episode VI shows an unfinished scene of Tifa Lockhart waking up in bed naked under a bedsheet, implied to be a case of <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UndressingTheUnconscious" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UndressingTheUnconscious">Undressing the Unconscious</a> after her fight with Hayate. Notably when she sits up the sheet stays glued to her chest up even without anything holding it up.
</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/RussellBrand" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/RussellBrand">Russell Brand</a> used this trope. <a class="urllink" href="http://fightthenewdrug.org/russell-brand-talks-sex-softcore-hardcore-porn/">In a video in which he talked about his pornography addiction,<img src="https://static.tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pub/external_link.gif" height="12" width="12" style="border:none;"></a> he covered himself with bedsheets while leaving his torso almost exposed.
</li></ul><p></p></div>
<p></p><div class="folderlabel" onclick="togglefolder('folder16');">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Western Animation&nbsp;</div><div id="folder16" class="folder" isfolder="true" style="display:block;">
<p></p><ul><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/Futurama" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/Futurama">Futurama</a></em>:
<ul><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ParodiedTrope" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ParodiedTrope">Parodied</a> in "<a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Recap/FuturamaS6E10ThePrisonerOfBenda" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Recap/FuturamaS6E10ThePrisonerOfBenda">The Prisoner of Benda</a>". Leela still has the "female" version of this despite the fact that <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FreakyFridayFlip" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FreakyFridayFlip">she's in the Professor's body</a>.
</li><li> Also happens with Morgan Proctor. She gets caught having sex with Fry in Bender's closet; she then runs out to catch a taxi with the bedsheet covering her when Bender figures out the truth about her. When Bender first walks in, she gasps and pulls the bedsheet up over her chest... and then Fry does the same thing.
</li></ul></li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/Gargoyles" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/Gargoyles">Gargoyles</a></em>: In "<a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Recap/GargoylesS2Heritage" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Recap/GargoylesS2Heritage">Heritage</a>", Elisa Maza and the Gargoyles are attacked by sea monsters and Eliza ends up falling into the water and washes up unconscious in Queen Florence Island. She's rescued by the villagers but <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CatchYourDeathOfCold" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CatchYourDeathOfCold">gets hypothermia</a> and the locals <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UndressingTheUnconscious" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UndressingTheUnconscious">undress her to get rid of her wet clothes</a> and tuck her in a bed and she stays nude under a bedsheet for a while until she's recovered.
</li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/HarleyQuinn2019" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/HarleyQuinn2019">Harley Quinn (2019)</a></em>:
<ul><li> In "<a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Recap/HarleyQuinn2019S1E2AHighBar" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Recap/HarleyQuinn2019S1E2AHighBar">A High Bar</a>", Ivy finds Kite-Man naked under the bedsheets in her bed, <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ReadyForLovemaking" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ReadyForLovemaking">Ready for Lovemaking</a> after their "date". She's quick to tell him to <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PleasePutSomeClothesOn" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PleasePutSomeClothesOn">Please Put Some Clothes On</a>.
</li><li> "<a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Recap/HarleyQuinn2019S2E9Bachelorette" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Recap/HarleyQuinn2019S2E9Bachelorette">Bachelorette</a>" shows Harley and Ivy both covered by a bedsheet when they wake up together after having sex.
</li></ul></li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/MyLittlePonyFriendshipIsMagic" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/MyLittlePonyFriendshipIsMagic">My Little Pony: Friendship Is Magic</a></em>: <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PlayedForLaughs" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PlayedForLaughs">Played for Laughs</a> in the teaser of "<a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Recap/MyLittlePonyFriendshipIsMagicS2E15TheSuperSpeedyCiderSqueezy6000" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Recap/MyLittlePonyFriendshipIsMagicS2E15TheSuperSpeedyCiderSqueezy6000">The Super Speedy Cider Squeezy 6000</a>", where Rainbow Dash wakes up Fluttershy, who <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SleepsInTheNude" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/SleepsInTheNude">Sleeps in the Nude</a>. Despite <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HalfDressedCartoonAnimal" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HalfDressedCartoonAnimal">clothing being a formal thing only in Equestria</a>&mdash;they're ponies, after all&mdash;Fluttershy has a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NakedFreakOut" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NakedFreakOut">Naked Freak-Out</a> and pulls the bedsheet up upon being awakened and when Rainbow removes it, she blushes and <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HandOrObjectUnderwear" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HandOrObjectUnderwear">cups her hooves</a> where her breasts <em>aren't</em>.
</li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/MoonbeamCity" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/MoonbeamCity">Moonbeam City</a></em>: In "Cop Con", Dazzle and Pizzaz <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheirFirstTime" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TheirFirstTime">first love scene together</a> has Pizzaz's skirt used as a Modesty Bedsheet for both her and Dazzle, whereas in their second, her right arm and the shredded window curtain barely cover the absolute minimum on her body. Dazzle is <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RightThroughHisPants" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/RightThroughHisPants">still wearing boxer briefs for some inexplicable reason</a>.
</li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/TheSimpsons" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/TheSimpsons">The Simpsons</a></em>:
<ul><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ParodiedTrope" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ParodiedTrope">Parodied</a> in one episode, with Homer's chest covered by the L-shaped sheet and Marge relying on strategically placed arms.
</li><li> Edna Krabbapel in one scene in which she is covered in a <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/SpiderMan" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/SpiderMan">Spider-Man</a> t-shirt (that's so large it might as well be a bedsheet) after having sex with Comic Book Guy in her apartment.
</li></ul></li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/StevenUniverseFuture" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/StevenUniverseFuture">Steven Universe: Future</a></em>: In "<a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Recap/StevenUniverseFutureS1E19IAmMyMonster" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Recap/StevenUniverseFutureS1E19IAmMyMonster">I Am My Monster</a>", after his <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Kaiju" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Kaiju">Kaiju</a> transformation <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShapeshiftingExcludesClothing" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShapeshiftingExcludesClothing">destroyed his clothing</a> Steven wakes up wearing only a blanket that someone presumably wrapped him in.
</li><li> <em><a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/SouthPark" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/SouthPark">South Park</a></em>:
<ul><li> In the episodes "<a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Recap/SouthParkS10E13GoGodGoXII" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Recap/SouthParkS10E13GoGodGoXII">Go God Go'' &amp; ''Go God Go XII</a>", when <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/UsefulNotes/RichardDawkins" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/UsefulNotes/RichardDawkins">Richard Dawkins</a> and Mr/s Garrison have sex, a bedsheet covers where all the "action" is.
</li><li> In Season 4, when Cartman's house is destroyed, a beam covers where Liane and "<a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UnfortunateNames" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/UnfortunateNames">Bill Cosby</a>" are having traditional sex.
</li></ul></li></ul><p></p></div>
